SIMPLE: fan-tan
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fan-tan
<hw>Fan"-tan`</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧n"t⟦acr⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Chinese (of Canton) in <ets>an-tan-kun</ets> gambling
house.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A Chinese gambling game in which coins or
other small objects are placed upon a table, usually under a cup, and
the players bet as to what remainder will be left when the sum of the
counters is divided by four.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A game with playing cards in which the cards are
played in sequences upon the table, the one who first gets rid of his
cards being the winner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fantasia</ent>⟦br⟧
